<TITLE> 3 'JMB men' arrested in Gaibandha </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gaibandha, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com)Three alleged activists of outlawed Islamist outfit Jama'atul Mujahideen Bangladesh were arrested on Wednesday night from Gaibandha villages, police said. bdnews24.com Gaibandha correspondent said police picked up three JMB activists from Bhatparha Gopalpur under Gaibandha Sadar Upazila and Talukkanupur and Parhakachua villages of Govindaganj upazila on Wednesday night. SM Shibli, Govindaganj police chief said, acting on a tip-off, police conducted raids first in Bhatparha Gopalpur village and arrested Rezaul Hasan Shihab, 25, son of Asadul Islam. Acting upon clues derived from Shihab, police raided Talukkanupur and Parhakachua villages and nabbed Al Amin, 20 and Manjurul Islam Manjil, 22 respectively. Of the arrestees, Rezaul Hasan happens to be an 'ehsaar' category member of JMB, who is also the northern regional commander of the banned militant outfit. During the hauls, police retrieved huge quantities of bomb ingredients, electronic equipment, batteries, grenade casings, chemicals and books from the spots. Police said at least 55 grenades could be made using the seized materials. The arrestees are being quizzed at Govindaganj Police Station. Police chief Shibli said a case has been filed with Govindaganj Police Station. Gaibandha police superintendent SM Moniruzzaman said without elaborating that the grenades were being made possibly for some 'special mission'. bdne
